pullRequest.title: CLDR-12002 move sandbox from und to mul
pullRequest.bodyText:
CLDR-12002

update UserRegistry to check SpecialLocales
cleanup some hard coded use of und
use 'root' as default from .js instead of und

nodes.bodyText: this is a fallback, for non-locale pages (such as the home screen)
we actually could have multiple sandbox locales… i.e. different scripts, etc… without needing to revisit this code.

afterCommit.message:
CLDR-12002 move sandbox from und to mul

Note: you will not find mul*.xml files checked in anywhere, This is on purpose.
they are generated dynamically with no content (just identity and a comment).

- update UserRegistry to check SpecialLocales
- cleanup some hard coded use of und
- use 'root' as default from .js instead of und
- do not require 'und' to exist
- move mul out of common AND seed to new 'sandbox' tree which is created automatically
- update SpecialLocales to provide a 'lite' id list
- remove some noise in tests
- update tests to be lenient on 'mul' locale
- add mul_AQ locale to sandbox also, since mul_ZZ is the default content.
- use mul_AQ for inheritance tests
- cleanup some SurveyMain code around locale ids

nodes.bodyText: Is it appropriate/intentional for this "testing" block to be added?
nodes.diffHunk:
@@ -3730,5 +3730,8 @@ not be patched by hand, as any changes made in that fashion may be lost.
 		<!--{ ?; Yi; ? } => { Sichuan Yi; Yi; China }-->
 		<likelySubtag from="und_Zanb" to="cmg_Zanb_MN"/>
 		<!--{ ?; Zanabazar Square; ? } => { Classical Mongolian; Zanabazar Square; Mongolia }-->
+
+		<!-- testing -->

nodes.bodyText: We've discussed putting .classpath and maybe .settings in .gitignore. This has been a problem since the Maven migration, since I can't run ST in eclipse without changing them. But I haven't checked in my changed versions. Is there any obstacle to adding them to .gitignore?

Ideally there might be a constant for the string literal "mul", referring to tr35 "The content contains more than one language or text that is simultaneously in multiple languages (such as brand names)."
If so maybe the comment "testing" could be expanded a bit

CLDR-12002 move sandbox from und to mul

- update SpecialLocales to provide a 'lite' id list
- remove some noise in tests
- update tests to be lenient on 'mul' locale
- add mul_AQ locale to sandbox also, since mul_ZZ is the default content.
- use mul_AQ for inheritance tests
- cleanup some SurveyMain code around locale ids
